---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Appliances & Systems">
  <span class="page-tag">Systems</span>
  <h1>Appliances &amp; Systems</h1>
  <p class="lead">Kitchen, heating, hot water, bathroom, dining, and water filtration.</p>

  <h2>Kitchen</h2>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Appliance</th><th>Spec</th><th>Links</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Cooktop</strong></td>
          <td>2-burner induction, 12" built-in, 120V</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.summitappliance.com/cooking/cooktops/induction" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Summit</a> · <a href="https://www.trueinduction.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">True Induction</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Oven</strong></td>
          <td>Breville Smart Oven Air Fryer Pro (BOV900) — 1800W</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.breville.com/en-us/product/bov900" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Breville BOV900</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Dishwasher</strong></td>
          <td>Fisher + Paykel single DishDrawer (DD24STI9N)</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.fisherpaykel.com/us/dishwashing/integrated-dishwashers/series-9-integrated-tall-single-dishdrawer-dishwasher-dd24sti9-n-82341.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">F+P product page</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Fridge/freezer</strong></td>
          <td>IKEA SUPERKALL built-in panel-ready, 8.8 cu ft</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.ikea.com/us/en/p/superkall-built-in-panel-ready-refrigerator-panel-ready-10462156/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IKEA SUPERKALL</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Washer/dryer</strong></td>
          <td>Compact 24" ventless combo — under stairs</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.bosch-home.com/us/products/washing-and-drying/washer-dryer-combos" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bosch combo W/D</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Range hood</strong></td>
          <td>Compact vent over cooktop for IAQ</td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Outdoor cooking</strong></td>
          <td>Propane stove/grill on covered porch</td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="note">
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> Bosch doesn't make a compact 2-burner induction cooktop. Summit and True Induction are the main options for 12" built-in 120V units.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Heating, Cooling &amp; Backup Cooking</h2>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th></th><th>Spec</th><th>Links</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Minisplit</strong></td>
          <td>9–12K BTU heat pump, interior wall mount</td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Wood stove — Option A</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Dwarf 5kW Cookstove Combo</strong> — cast iron cooktop + 9&times;9&times;8" baking oven + direct air intake box. EPA certified, 30–35k BTU, 4" flue, 150 lbs. Rear flue exit for max cooktop. ~$1,500 + ~$100 air intake</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.tinywoodstove.com/product/dwarf-cookstove/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dwarf Cookstove</a> · <a href="https://www.tinywoodstove.com/product/fresh-air-intake/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Air intake</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Wood stove — Option B</strong></td>
          <td><strong>Steelhead</strong> — 14&times;14" cooktop, accepts 18" logs, UL certified, 6" flue, 180 lbs. Optional 10-gallon hot water tank. Fresh air intake. Burns up to 8 hrs.</td>
          <td><a href="https://flameinnovation.com/product/steelhead-small-wood-stove/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Steelhead</a></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="decision">
    <p><strong>Stove decision:</strong> Dwarf = smaller cooktop but adds baking oven for real backup cooking (bread, casseroles). Steelhead = larger cooktop + plug-and-play hot water when stove is running. Both have direct air intake capability (critical for tight tiny house).</p>
  </div>

  <p><strong>Hot water from Dwarf option:</strong> DIY copper coil heat exchanger can be wrapped around the outside of the 4" flue pipe to pre-heat domestic hot water via thermosiphon. Most commercial stovepipe heat exchangers (Hilkoil, Vogelzang) are made for 5–6" flue pipes and won't fit the Dwarf's 4" flue directly — so this is a DIY project. Worth contacting Tiny Wood Stove (<a href="mailto:support@tinywoodstove.com">support@tinywoodstove.com</a>) to ask if they're developing a water heating accessory.</p>

  <p>The Steelhead's 6" flue accepts standard commercial heat exchangers, and its integrated 10-gallon tank is plug-and-play — a real advantage if hot water from the stove matters.</p>

  <h2>Hot Water</h2>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th></th><th>Spec</th><th>Links</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Bathroom</strong></td>
          <td>AO Smith EJC-10 (10 gal) or Bosch Tronic ES8 (7 gal) — 120V</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.hotwater.com/products/compact-proline/ejc-10-200/100118329.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AO Smith EJC-10</a> · <a href="https://www.bosch-homecomfort.com/us/en/ocs/residential/tronic-3000t-1098972-p/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bosch Tronic</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Kitchen</strong></td>
          <td>Stiebel Eltron SHC 2.5 — 120V plug</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.stiebel-eltron-usa.com/products/shc-mini-tank-electric-water-heaters" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stiebel Eltron SHC</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Expansion</strong></td>
          <td>Space for second bathroom tank in series if needed</td>
          <td></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p>Series connection preferred over parallel (pre-heating benefit, simpler plumbing).</p>

